h1. Certificate Lifecycle Monitoring - OpenBao PKI

{panel:title=Monitoring Overview|borderStyle=solid|borderColor=#1976d2|titleBGColor=#e3f2fd|bgColor=#f1f8f4}
*Purpose:* Track certificate issuance, expiration, revocation, and PKI health
*Approach:* Multi-layered monitoring using scripts, audit logs, Prometheus, and Grafana
*Update Frequency:* Real-time (Prometheus) + Daily Reports (Scripts)
{panel}

----

h2. Monitoring Architecture

{code:title=Monitoring Stack}
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  Monitoring Layers                      │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                         │
│  Layer 1: OpenBao Native Audit Logs                    │
│  ├─ All PKI operations logged                          │
│  ├─ Certificate issuance events                        │
│  └─ Revocation events                                  │
│                                                         │
│  Layer 2: Scheduled Monitoring Scripts                 │
│  ├─ Certificate expiration checker                     │
│  ├─ CRL (Certificate Revocation List) analysis         │
│  └─ PKI health validator                               │
│                                                         │
│  Layer 3: Prometheus Metrics Exporter                  │
│  ├─ Real-time certificate counts                       │
│  ├─ Expiration alerts                                  │
│  └─ PKI mount health status                            │
│                                                         │
│  Layer 4: Grafana Dashboards                           │
│  ├─ Visual certificate lifecycle tracking              │
│  ├─ Expiration timeline charts                         │
│  └─ Alert notifications (Slack/Email)                  │
│                                                         │
│  Layer 5: Cert-Manager Monitoring (Kubernetes)         │
│  ├─ Certificate resource status                        │
│  ├─ ACME challenge tracking                            │
│  └─ Automatic renewal metrics                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
{code}

----

h2. Layer 1: OpenBao Audit Logging

h3. Enable Audit Logging

{code:language=bash|title=Enable File-Based Audit Log}
# Enable audit device
bao audit enable file file_path=/var/log/openbao/audit.log

# Or for Kubernetes deployment, use stdout
kubectl exec -n openbao openbao-0 -- \
  bao audit enable file file_path=stdout
{code}

h3. Audit Log Structure

{code:language=json|title=Sample PKI Certificate Issuance Event}
{
  "time": "2026-02-07T01:52:00Z",
  "type": "response",
  "auth": {
    "token_type": "service",
    "policies": ["default", "pki-admin"]
  },
  "request": {
    "operation": "update",
    "path": "pki_int/issue/acme-default",
    "data": {
      "common_name": "testserver.solar.energy.internal",
      "ttl": "720h"
    }
  },
  "response": {
    "data": {
      "certificate": "-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----...",
      "serial_number": "4e:4c:f1:78:45:74:74:ce"
    }
  }
}
{code}

h3. Query Audit Logs for PKI Events

{code:language=bash|title=Extract Certificate Issuance Events}
# Filter PKI operations from audit log
cat /var/log/openbao/audit.log | \
  jq 'select(.request.path | startswith("pki_int/")) | 
      {time, operation: .request.operation, path: .request.path, 
       common_name: .request.data.common_name}'

# Count certificate issuances per day
cat /var/log/openbao/audit.log | \
  jq -r 'select(.request.path | contains("/issue/")) | .time' | \
  cut -d'T' -f1 | sort | uniq -c
{code}

----

h2. Layer 2: Scheduled Monitoring Script

h3. Monitoring Script Features

|| Feature || Description || Output ||
| Certificate Expiration | Checks days remaining for all certs | Color-coded status (Valid/Expiring/Expired) |
| CRL Analysis | Tracks revoked certificates | Revocation count and CRL freshness |
| PKI Health Check | Validates mount accessibility | Mount status (Healthy/Unhealthy) |
| ACME Endpoint Status | Verifies ACME directory availability | Active/Inactive status |
| Prometheus Export | Generates metrics in Prometheus format | {{pki_metrics.prom}} |

h3. Execution and Scheduling

{code:language=bash|title=Run Monitoring Script}
# Manual execution
./monitor_certificate_lifecycle.sh

# Schedule with cron (daily at 9 AM)
crontab -e
# Add line:
0 9 * * * /path/to/monitor_certificate_lifecycle.sh

# Kubernetes CronJob example
apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: CronJob
metadata:
  name: pki-lifecycle-monitor
spec:
  schedule: "0 9 * * *"
  jobTemplate:
    spec:
      template:
        spec:
          containers:
          - name: monitor
            image: openbao:latest
            command: ["/scripts/monitor_certificate_lifecycle.sh"]
{code}

