h2. Layer 4: Grafana Dashboards

h3. Dashboard Panels

{panel:title=Certificate Lifecycle Dashboard|bgColor=#f5f5f5}
*Panel 1: Certificate Count Overview*
- Total certificates issued (all-time)
- Valid certificates (current)
- Expiring soon (< 30 days)
- Expired certificates

*Panel 2: Expiration Timeline*
- Bar chart showing certificate expiration distribution
- X-axis: Days until expiration (buckets: 0-7, 8-30, 31-90, 90+)
- Y-axis: Certificate count

*Panel 3: PKI Health Status*
- Single stat panels for each PKI mount
- Green/Red status indicators
- ACME endpoint availability

*Panel 4: Revocation Tracking*
- Time series of revoked certificates
- Spike detection for security incidents

*Panel 5: ACME Activity*
- Certificate issuance rate (per hour/day)
- ACME challenge success/failure rate
- Average issuance time
{panel}

h3. Sample Grafana Queries

{code:language=promql|title=PromQL Queries for Dashboards}
# Total valid certificates
sum(openbao_pki_cert_valid_count)

# Certificates expiring in next 30 days
sum(openbao_pki_cert_expiring_count{threshold_days="30"})

# Certificate issuance rate (per hour)
rate(openbao_pki_cert_valid_count[1h]) * 3600

# PKI mount health percentage
(sum(openbao_pki_mount_health) / count(openbao_pki_mount_health)) * 100

# ACME endpoint uptime (last 24h)
avg_over_time(openbao_pki_acme_endpoint_health[24h]) * 100
{code}

h3. Dashboard JSON Export

{info:title=Dashboard Import}
A complete Grafana dashboard JSON can be imported for instant visualization. Key features:
* Auto-refresh every 60 seconds
* Drill-down capability for certificate details
* Alert state indicators
* Historical trending (last 7/30/90 days)
{info}

