h2. Layer 5: Cert-Manager Monitoring (Kubernetes)

h3. Certificate Resource Status

{code:language=bash|title=Monitor Cert-Manager Certificates}
# List all certificates and their status
kubectl get certificates -A

# Check specific certificate details
kubectl describe certificate solar-panel-cert

# View cert-manager pod logs
kubectl logs -n cert-manager deployment/cert-manager -f
{code}

h3. Certificate Status Conditions

|| Condition || Meaning || Action ||
| {{Ready=True}} | Certificate issued and valid | ✅ No action |
| {{Ready=False}}, {{Issuing=True}} | Certificate being issued | ⏳ Wait for completion |
| {{Ready=False}}, {{Reason=Expired}} | Certificate expired | ⚠️ Check renewal configuration |
| {{Ready=False}}, {{Reason=Failed}} | Issuance failed | ❌ Check ACME challenge logs |

h3. Cert-Manager Prometheus Metrics

{code:language=promql|title=Cert-Manager Queries}
# Certificates by readiness status
sum by (condition) (certmanager_certificate_ready_status)

# Certificate expiration time
certmanager_certificate_expiration_timestamp_seconds - time()

# ACME order success rate
rate(certmanager_http_acme_order_total{status="valid"}[5m]) /
rate(certmanager_http_acme_order_total[5m])
{code}

----

h2. Complete Monitoring Workflow

{code:title=Daily Monitoring Routine}
09:00 - Automated Script Execution
     ├─ Run monitor_certificate_lifecycle.sh
     ├─ Generate report & Prometheus metrics
     └─ Email report to PKI team

Real-time - Prometheus Scraping
     ├─ Scrape pki_metrics.prom every 60s
     ├─ Evaluate alert rules
     └─ Push to Alertmanager

Continuous - Grafana Dashboards
     ├─ Display current certificate status
     ├─ Show expiration timeline
     └─ Track ACME issuance activity

On Alert - Incident Response
     ├─ Slack/Email notification sent
     ├─ On-call engineer investigates
     └─ Remediation (renew/revoke/etc.)

Weekly - Management Review
     ├─ Review trends (issuance rate, revocations)
     ├─ Validate certificate policy compliance
     └─ Plan capacity (storage, performance)
{code}

----

h2. Key Monitoring Metrics

h3. Certificate Expiration Tracking

|| Metric || Threshold || Alert Level ||
| Days until Root CA expires | < 365 days | Critical |
| Days until Intermediate CA expires | < 180 days | Critical |
| Leaf certificates expiring | < 30 days | Warning |
| Leaf certificates expiring | < 7 days | Critical |

h3. Operational Health

|| Metric || Threshold || Alert Level ||
| PKI mount inaccessible | Any failure | Critical |
| ACME endpoint down | > 2 minutes | Warning |
| CRL not updated | > 24 hours | Warning |
| Certificate issuance failure rate | > 5% | Warning |
| Certificate storage growth | > 10,000/day | Info |

h3. Security Indicators

|| Metric || Threshold || Alert Level ||
| Certificate revocation spike | > 10/hour | Critical |
| Unauthorized PKI access attempts | Any | Critical |
| Weak key algorithm usage | Any RSA < 2048 | Warning |
| Certificate issued outside policy | Any | Critical |

----

h2. Troubleshooting Guide

h3. Certificate Not Renewing

{panel:title=Diagnosis Steps|bgColor=#fff3e0}
# Check cert-manager logs for ACME challenge failures
# Verify DNS resolution for domain
# Ensure ACME endpoint is accessible from cluster
# Check firewall rules for http-01 challenges
# Validate role configuration (allowed_domains, max_ttl)
{panel}

h3. High Revocation Rate

{panel:title=Investigation Steps|bgColor=#ffebee}
# Review audit logs for revocation requests
# Identify pattern: specific issuer, domain, or time period
# Check for security incidents (compromised keys)
# Validate revocation was intentional (system decommission, rotation)
# Update CRL distribution if needed
{panel}

h3. PKI Mount Unhealthy

{panel:title=Resolution Steps|bgColor=#ffebee}
# Check OpenBao server status: {{bao status}}
# Verify mount exists: {{bao secrets list}}
# Check storage backend connectivity
# Review OpenBao server logs for errors
# Remount if necessary (with caution - may lose data)
{panel}

----

h2. Best Practices

{tip:title=Monitoring Best Practices}
# *Set appropriate thresholds*: 30 days for leaf certs, 180 days for CAs
# *Enable multiple alert channels*: Slack, email, PagerDuty
# *Retain monitoring data*: Keep at least 90 days of metrics
# *Regular reviews*: Weekly check of dashboards and trends
# *Automate remediation*: Use cert-manager for auto-renewal
# *Test alerting*: Simulate expiring certificates to verify alerts fire
# *Document runbooks*: Clear procedures for each alert type
# *Audit compliance*: Ensure monitoring meets regulatory requirements
{tip}

